## 📝 Enrollment

### Purpose
Links a Student to a Course and tracks their progress.

### Attributes
| Attribute | Type | Description |
|-----------|------|-------------|
| enrollment_id | int | Unique identifier |
| student | User | The student |
| course | Course | The course |
| status | EnrollmentStatus | ENROLLED/COMPLETED/DROPPED |
| enrolled_at | datetime | When they enrolled |
| submodule_progress | Dict[int, bool] | submodule_id → completed |
| quiz_scores | Dict[int, float] | quiz_id → best score |

### Methods
| Method | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| `mark_submodule_complete(id)` | Mark a submodule as done |
| `record_quiz_score(id, score)` | Record quiz attempt (keeps best) |
| `get_progress_percent()` | Overall completion % |
| `is_course_complete()` | All submodules + all quizzes passed? |
| `complete_course()` | Mark as COMPLETED, issue certificate |

### Progress Calculation:
```python
def get_progress_percent(self) -> float:
    total_submodules = len(self.submodule_progress)
    completed = sum(1 for done in self.submodule_progress.values() if done)
    return (completed / total_submodules) * 100 if total_submodules > 0 else 0

def is_course_complete(self) -> bool:
    all_submodules_done = all(self.submodule_progress.values())
    all_quizzes_passed = all(score >= 70 for score in self.quiz_scores.values())
    return all_submodules_done and all_quizzes_passed
```

